solutions.content:
**OBSERVATION :**
For any Tree, the Preorder traversal is of this type : 
| root | left subtree | right subtree |

So, if we are able to identify the index of ending of left subtree in the given vector preorder.
Then, we can easily defferentiate the left subtree part with the right subtree part and build the rest of the tree using recursion.

Now, for BSTs we know that the elements present on the left subtree are smaller than the root and elements present on the right subtree are greater than the root. And the 0th index is root itself.

So, if we find the last element in the preorder which is smaller than the 0th indexed element (say, 'pos'). We can say that from 1th index to index 'pos' lies the left subtree, from index 'pos' to last index lies the right subtree and the 0th element is our root node.

**INTUTION :**
Traversal through : int l , int r. Meaning left most index and right most index of vector preorder.
First element is root i.e. element on 'l' index.
Find the last element in the whole vector which is smaller then the root value and store the index value in 'pos'.
Let Recursion make the rest of the left subtree from index l+1 to pos.
Let Recursion make the rest of the left subtree from index pos+1 to r.
BASE CASE : if l crosses r, i.e. l>r then return NULL.

**TIME COMPLEXITY : O(N)**
**SPACE COMPLEXITY : O(N) + O(N)** Consturcting the BST + Recursive Stack

**CODE :**
```
class Solution {
public:
    TreeNode* helper(vector<int>& arr,int l,int r){
		//BASE CASE
        if(l>r)
            return NULL;

		//First element is root itself
        TreeNode *root=new TreeNode(arr[l]);

        int pos=l;     //For corner case that only 1 element is given it the array
        for(int i=l+1; i<=r; i++){   //Find the index of last element which is smaller than the root node
            if(arr[i]<root->val)
                pos=i;
            else
                break;
        }
        root->left=helper(arr,l+1,pos);  //Make left subtree
        root->right=helper(arr,pos+1,r); //Make right subtree
        return root;
    }
    TreeNode* bstFromPreorder(vector<int>& preorder) {
        int l=0;                  //Left most element of array
		int r=preorder.size()-1;  //Right most element of the array
        return helper(preorder,l,r);
    }
};
```

