solutions.content:
**INTUTION:-**
1.WE KNOW THAT IN BINARY TREE ALL THE NODES TO THE LEFT OF ROOT HAVE LESSER VALUE THAN ROOT AND ALL THE RIGHT ELEMENT HAVE GREATER THAN ROOT VALUE. 
2.IN THE QUESTION PREORDER TRAVERSAL IS GIVEN WHICH IS **ROOT LEFT RIGHT**  SO THE FIRST ELEMENT WILL BE ROOT OF THE TREE => preorder[0] is the root of given tree.  
     **preorder traversal list can be seen as =>    [root, left subtree values, right subtree values]** 
	 so when we iterate on the preorder list to see the left and right subtree, see where root value is lesser than preorder[i]. So here we got the index of start of right subtree and ending of the left subtree.
	 **some special cases;-**
	 *preorder list ->[root, left subtree, no right subtree] or [root, no left subtree, right subtree]*
	 for this case we need to find the ending of the left subtree but 
	 ``for(int i = start; i < end; i++) {
            if(preorder[start] < preorder[i]) {
                leftend = i;
                break;
            }
        }``
		this loop can not find the leftend index for this case so we need to initaize the leftend index before this loop so after if we not find any right subtree we can directly get it. and if we found out right subtree than leftend will be changed by loop.
		write before the loop 
		`int leftend = end;`
**ALGORITHM AND FULL CODE:-**
```
class Solution {
public:
    TreeNode* helper(vector<int>& preorder, int start, int end) {
        if(start == end) {
            return NULL;
        }     
        TreeNode* root = new TreeNode(preorder[start], NULL, NULL);
        int leftend = end;
        for(int i = start; i < end; i++) {
            if(preorder[start] < preorder[i]) {
                leftend = i;
                break;
            }
        }
        root->left = helper(preorder, start+1,leftend);
        root->right = helper(preorder, leftend, end);
        return root;
    }
    TreeNode* bstFromPreorder(vector<int>& preorder) {
        return helper(preorder, 0, preorder.size());
    }
};
```
