**Intuition:**
We want to XOR N's binary with an array of 1's of the same length.
**Approach:**
Find out how long N is (via while loop.... 2^y=N).
Then we subtract 1 from our number, and we will get an array of 1's in binary.
(ie. if x=2^8, then x-1 in binary is "1111 1111").



