Subtract N from this number and you will get the bits to the right that are 0 converted to 1, which is what you are looking for, e.g. 010 as input, 011 as the number you calculate, 011-010 = 001. There is only one edge case for this solution at N == 0. 

    def bitwiseComplement(self, N: int) -> int:
        if N == 0: 
            return 1
        else:
            return 2**(int(log2(N))+1)-1 - N

