# Approach
Using Bitwise Operator

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$$O(logn)$$

- Space complexity:
$$O(1)$$

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int bitwiseComplement(int n) {
        int num = n;
        int mask = 0;
        if (n == 0)
            return 1;
        while (num != 0) {
            mask = (mask << 1) | 1;
            num = num >> 1;    
        }
        int ans = (~n) & mask;
        return ans;
    }
};
```

