class Solution {
    //TC : O(N)

    /*
    Concept:
    % operator gives us how much more he have than required. Like if we have 70%60 than we get 10.
    Here 10 tells us that we have 10 extra . For 120%60 we have 0 extra. This extra will range between 0 to 59. 
    For this question we would consider a pair as answer if sum of extra is 0 or 60.

    Algorithm :
    We will keep a remainder array to keep count of remainders.
    Now let's traverse array.Consider we get an element 40.We will then find extra of 40,which will come out as 40.
	Now we will check how many numbers we have previously seen with remainder as 
    60-40=20.If count comes out as 2 than we will have 2 pairs as answer and add 2 in our count variable.
	There is one exception if remainder comes as 0.
	Then we can't find if there is someone with remainder 60-0=60.We need to find numbers with remainder as 0.
	We will make array of size 60,since remainders can only be between 0 to 59.
    */

    public int numPairsDivisibleBy60(int[] time) {
        int[] rem=new int[60];  //to keep count of remainders
        int count=0;
        for(int t:time){
            if(t%60==0)
                count+=rem[0];
            else
                count+=rem[60-t%60];
            rem[t%60]++;
        }
        return count;
    }
}
```

