To make a pair , both the elements modulus should leave reminder 0 on adding.

So, If 1st element leaves reminder **X** and 2nd element of pair leaves reminder **Y** thn in order to be a valid pair it must satisfy **Y = 60-X** ;

Suppose, We have a pair **[140,220]**,

Then there reminder with 60 will be **[20,40]**

Clearly, if X = 20 and Y = 40 , then to be a valid Pair with  **Y** should equal to **60-X** i.e **60-20** i.e **40** which makes up a valid pair.

We are increasing the pair ans only if we get  compliment modulo for that number.

Also, in case the reminder is 0 that means the number is fully divisible by 60 which means the no. of elements having reminder 0 will add up to ans on each founding and the freq will increase by 1. 
Thus, if we got 3 elements with reminder as 0 , thn the total Pairs will be 2+1 
Eg: if we have [60, 120, 80] then, the valid pairs will be 
[60,120],
[60,180],
[120,180]
giving as as 2 + 1 + 0 i.e 3 pairs.

